hrough some pet command even.<br><br>I'm all for it. I've always thought pets should have a larger role in raids.<br><br>Tal<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyanelinthedrunken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YanelintheDrunken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/02 3:49:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Fire Pets: Imbicilic Wizards</span><hr size=1> erm Grimstaff Iwan is talking about the L52 and 58 fire pets.  The DS they have is the very same one you can cast.  From the great love i have heard about its amazing newbie powers i think that part can be overlooked on that pet.  Furthermore the fighting skills of the wizard pets are subpar compared to all the other pets near its spell level.<br><br>Its only redeeming virtue as a pet is that once in a while the wizard pet won't fight and will start chaining stun/interuppt spells...<br><br>My vote however is to leave the pets as is and simply force all of them to have the name Al'Kabor...and maybe be crappier to live up to the name. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucalinot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calinot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/02 10:47:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> They already have it</span><hr size=1> If the pets are level 44+ then they already have access to the spell. Pet is just too dumb to cast it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/02 8:47:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They already have it</span><hr size=1> &quot;erm Grimstaff Iwan is talking about the L52 and 58 fire pets. The DS they have is the very same one you can cast.&quot;<br><br>Really?  Seems to me I recall Magicians can cast damage shields at that level that seem to be a little bit more potent, maybe I was mistaken... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/02 6:19:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/neriakwraith.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They already have it</span><hr size=1> Mage fire pets from level 1 to 49 have a DS that is = to it's level + 2 damage per hit. So the level 49 pet should have a DS that does 51 damage per hit.<br>The 52 and 58 fire pet is more like a wizard than the former versions, in that they cast a damage absorbtion skin, and a damage shield (I think it's O`Keils' to tell the truth). That means that their 52 and 58 fire pet sucks ass compared to their 49 fire pet.<br> <p><CENTER><EMBED src="http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/barcode.swf" quality=high bgcolor=#000000  WIDTH="220" HEIGHT="60" NAME="barcode" ALIGN="" TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer"></EMBED></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/02 8:29:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They already have it</span><hr size=1> Actually since the Mage can cast their Cadeau of Flame on the pet at that level (33 pt damage shield) I'd say that is a pretty moot point.  Mages don't need irresistable blasts of any sort or level, they have damage that bypasses resistances. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyanelinthedrunken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YanelintheDrunken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/7/02 6:50:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Fire Pets: Imbicilic Wizards</span><hr size=1> &quot;Actually since the Mage can cast their Cadeau of Flame on the pet at that level (33 pt damage shield) I'd say that is a pretty moot point. Mages don't need irresistable blasts of any sort or level, they have damage that bypasses resistances.&quot;<br><br>First off an annoying technicallity: Cadeau of Flame is not L52 it is L56 which means for the first wizard pet one must assume they would be using the L49 DS for 25 dmg.  It is also asinine to discuss its potential to be damage shielded as i personaly have tanked and survived longer as a mage than the pet in question.<br><br>That is all of course beyond the point you were reffering to total non-resistable mage DPS, which i didn't get immediately (slow mage and all.)<br><br>Assuming the we have our mod-rod vending mages 56+ fighting a high resist mob only 1 of them will be doing significant damage.  That is the one who cast the DS.  Mages are in the same boat as necros as far as stacking damage is conscerned.  When our spells are useless one mage will have any DPS other than pet DPS.<br><br>Now lets leave that be for now.  Generally with raids where a mage would required to be a vending machine you will need more than one mage.  Swarming mana hungry casters is not a good or effiecent thing for a single mage so at least one mage would be needing to focus entirely on his pet.<br><br>Now we have the pet doing the damage for its master as long as the master is too swamped making rods to be able to cast.  At L44 how easily could you nuke a L60? Let alone a really high mob with any sort of resists.  Adding a lure to the wizard pet would allow it to cast and hit with some of its spells.  Why would you do that instead of summoing a meaner more damaging pet? ...erm  its cute? insanely high AC or damage reducing curses?   I don't really see many places where a mage couldn't do more damage without a lure casting pet but i might not be seeing everything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/7/02 10:21:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Fire Pets: Imbicilic Wizards</span><hr size=1> I never said the spell was level 56, I said it was available to cast at that level, which it is.  Further, since you have a fraction of your pet's hps and AC I find it highly doubtful you can out tank your pet.  You are concerned your pet gets his spells resisted, which is a meaningless concern since they hit just fine and the great majority of damage that they do totally bypasses resistances.  I'll give you a little clue that as a Mage you probably are unaware of but Enticement of Flame gets resisted, and resisted a LOT by creatures level 60+, so it wouldn't even help you that much.  It's not as 'unresistable' as normal Lure spells, not to mention that its fire based so anything with heavy resistances to fire (not too many of THOSE out there at those levels eh?) pretty much shrug it off.<br><br>Magicians do not need lure spells, not back door lure spells, not pet lure spells, not any.  The reason Wizards get them is that resistances shut Wizards OFF, we contribute nothing.  Magicians are hurt by resistances, but still contribute rather well - and the way pets have been worked on recently there's even LESS reason to complain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulonewar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LoneWar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/10/02 12:46:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Fire Pets: Imbicilic Wizards</span><hr size=1> Grimstaff,<br><br>Although you are extremely knowledgable about most things, I must point out some flaws.<br><br>First, a level 60 Rod mage can have more hit points then their level 58 Fire Pet, especially one in an uber guild.<br><br>Second, do to these low hit points, the 58 fire pet is not effective to put a damage shield on and let it get hit, having watched fights with this pet, and other Mage pets against level 44 to 46 Sun Revenants in Scarlet desert, this pet lasts about 1/4 the time that any other pet lasts.<br><br>And finally, this pet (prior to the increased pet damage change) hit for low to mid 40s, compared to standard pets hitting in the 60s. And it was only rarely hitting for them.<br><br>And as for outtanking pets, Hit Points and AC are nothing compared to level, and next to this pet as it stands, any mage that CANT out tank it needs to spend a bit more time on gear.<br><br>That is how bad this pet is.<br><br>And considering that mages are Fire/Magic based, I dont see how taking their by far weakest pet, and giving it a spell in line with its level, class, and abilities is in any way out of line. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umudsquirti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mudsquirti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/12/02 11:29:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=745